place.name: KNOCKBAIN
place.gazetteerText: Knockbain, par., SE. Ross and Cromarty, on N. side of Beauly Firth, 12,035 ac., pop. 1866; P.O.; the church is 5 miles (by Kessock Ferry) NW. of Inverness. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)

place.name: KNOCK
place.gazetteerText: Knock (or Eye or Uie), quoad sacra par., Stornoway par., Ross-shire, pop. 2990; comprises Eye peninsula, on E. side of Lewis island, and contains Swordle and Knock, vil., 5 miles SE. of Stornoway, pop. 496. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
